The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 28 September is 75,917 (8,749.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 September, there were 2,166 new confirmed cases (249.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 September, there were 1,480 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 46% (686 extra cases).
